verbose_text: Somatic, reproductive and metabolic indices were evaluated in the above groups, including body weight (BW) gain during the course of the study; vaginal opening (VO), as consensus external marker of puberty in female rats; estrous cyclicity in adulthood; basal serum LH and FSH levels; basal insulin and glucose levels; and body fat composition (Fat)--the latter was conducted by quantitative magnetic resonance, using the EchoMRITM 700 analyzer (Houston, TX, USA software v.2.0), using validated protocols at our laboratory.
